 for bestpractices and # Admin Dashboard (Concierge)

## Overview
Create a premium, editorially-styled Admin Dashboard (Concierge) for Roam Resort that enables concierge admins to monitor high-level metrics, view recent inquiries, apply quick filters, and access shortcuts to inquiry management tasks. Extend with an Admin CSV Export / Reports capability to export inquiries and reconciliation data to CSV for offline processing and accounting. Include an Admin Inquiry List with robust filters, search, and bulk export actions. The UI must be visually luxurious, performant, accessible, and strictly guard against runtime nulls and undefined values as described in the mandatory coding standards.

---

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- The Admin Dashboard (Concierge) is the concierge landing hub. It presents at-a-glance health metrics, a feed of the most recent inquiries, and quick actions/shortcuts to common admin tasks. It serves as the gateway to the Inquiry management workflow, including exporting data (CSV), creating internal notes, and initiating payment reconciliation steps.

Goals:
- Deliver a calm, premium landing experience that surfaces high-priority metrics, a live-ish feed of recent inquiries, and fast-access actions.
- Provide seamless access to export functionality (CSV) for inquiries and reconciliation data.
- Provide a launchpad to the deeper Admin Inquiry List with advanced filters, search, and bulk export.

Connected features:
- Admin CSV Export / Reports: Export inquiries and reconciliation data to CSV for offline processing and accounting.
- Admin Inquiry List: A dedicated list view with filters, search, and bulk export actions.

UI elements and how they need to look:
- Overview Cards: 
  - New Inquiries (count)
  - Pending Payments (count)
  - Confirmed (count)
  - Revenue (manual input or calculated from reconciliation state)
  - Average Response Time (calculated metric)
- Recent Inquiries Feed: a compact feed showing latest inquiries with key fields (inquiry id, guest name, destination, dates, status, and quick actions like Open Details or Create Payment Link).
- Quick Filters: chips or segmented controls to filter by status, destination, date range, etc.
- Shortcuts: prominent action buttons for CSV export, Create Manual Note, and Reconcile Payments.
- Data Visualization: lightweight charts or small stat blocks illustrating trends (e.g., inquiries over time, payments pending).
- Global search/quick access: top-right search to jump to inquiries or dashboards.

UI specifics:
- Consistent with Roam Resort’s design system: deep navy backgrounds, warm beige content areas, bronze-gold accents, editorial typography, generous spacing, and refined card visuals.
- Interactions: hover states on cards, responsive layouts, accessible controls with clear focus styles, and smooth transitions.

API integrations:
- No external APIs beyond internal app services; all data accessed via internal API endpoints for inquiries, payments, and reconciliation.
- Ensure data shaping guards and default values if API returns null.

---

## Components to Build
- AdminDashboardConciergePage
  - Layout wrapper with header navigation, metrics area, recent inquiries feed, quick filters, and shortcuts.
- MetricCard
  - Reusable card showing title, value, and optional subtitle; supports statuses and icons.
- RecentInquiriesFeed
  - List with virtualization-friendly rendering, per-item actions, and status badges; handles empty state gracefully.
- QuickFiltersBar
  - Interactive chips/segmented controls to filter inquiry data quickly.
- ShortcutsPanel
  - Action buttons for: Export CSV, Create Manual Note, Reconcile Payments.
- CsvExportModal (or inline modal)
  - Configure export scope (inquiries, reconciliation data), date range, and export button.
- AdminInquiryListLink
  - Link to Admin Inquiry List page (for navigation consistency).
- AdminInquiryListPage
  - Filterable, searchable list of all inquiries with bulk actions and CSV export.
- AdminInquiryListToolbar
  - Filters (status, destination, date range), search input, and bulk actions.
- AdminInquiryListTable
  - Paginated table with safe data rendering and per-row actions (Open, Edit, Export).
- AdminInquiryDetailDrawer (optional)
  - Quick view to see a selected inquiry in a drawer for detail without navigation.
- DataVisualizationPanel
  - Lightweight charts (line/bar) using bronze-gold and navy accents to show trends.

Technical details per component:
- Each component must accept and defensively handle data that could be null or undefined and use data ?? [] patterns or guards.
- Use Array.isArray() guards when mapping or filtering.
- Initialize React state for arrays as useState<Type[]>([]).
- Ensure all API-derived data is validated with Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [] or equivalent.

---

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Pages:
  - Admin Dashboard (Concierge)
  - Admin Inquiry List (with filters, search, and bulk export)
- Components:
  - Reusable metric cards, feed items, charts, filters, and actions with accessible ARIA labels.
- State management:
  - Local component state for UI interactions; consider a lightweight context or store for cross-page state if needed (but avoid over-engineering).
- Data handling:
  - Fetch data from internal endpoints (examples below) with robust null handling:
    - Inquiries: GET /api/admin/inquiries
    - Reconciliation: GET /api/admin/reconciliations
    - Exports: POST /api/admin/export (payload defines type: inquiries or reconciliations, filters)
  - All responses should be validated; use const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
- CSV export:
  - Implement client-side CSV generation for both inquiries and reconciliation data, with proper headers and encoding.
  - Allow server-side export as a fallback with a download URL.

- Routing:
  - /admin/concierge (Dashboard)
  - /admin/inquiries (Admin Inquiry List)

- Accessibility:
  - Keyboard navigable controls, proper semantic HTML (roles, aria-labels), and readable color contrast per the palette.

### Backend
- Endpoints:
  - GET /api/admin/inquiries
    - Supports query params: status, destination, dateFrom, dateTo, search, page, pageSize
  - GET /api/admin/reconciliations
    - Supports similar filters as above
  - POST /api/admin/export
    - Body: { type: 'inquiries' | 'reconciliations', filters?: object, format?: 'csv' }
    - Returns: { url: string } or a generated CSV blob
  - GET /api/admin/inquiries/:id
    - For detail view
  - POST /api/admin/inquiries/:id/notes
    - Add internal notes
  - PATCH /api/admin/inquiries/:id/status
    - Update status
- Database models:
  - Inquiries: id, guestName, destinationId, destinationName, dates, guests, status, createdAt, updatedAt, paymentStatus, amount, currency, etc.
  - Reconciliations: id, inquiryId, amount, currency, status, reconciledAt, notes
  - Destinations: id, name, slug
  - InternalNotes: id, inquiryId, note, createdAt, authorId
- Data validation:
  - All inputs sanitized; status enums validated; date formats standardized.
- Security:
  - Admin authentication required; role-based access (Concierge Admin) for export and list endpoints.
  - Validate user permissions on every admin route.

### Integration
- Frontend calls to the internal API layer with consistent error handling and loading states.
- Data normalization layer to shape raw API responses into arrays for rendering.
- State flows:
  - Dashboard fetches metrics + recent inquiries; clicking a recent item navigates to detail or opens a modal.
  - Quick filters refine the dataset, updating both the dashboard feed and the Admin Inquiry List.
  - CSV export endpoints accept filter parameters from both pages to generate aligned datasets.
- Data consistency:
  - Ensure that exports reflect the same filters as visible on the dashboard/list to maintain parity.

---

## User Experience Flow
1. Concierge logs into Admin Panel.
2. Lands on Admin Dashboard (Concierge) showing:
   - Overview metrics (New Inquiries, Pending Payments, Confirmed, Revenue, Avg Response Time)
   - Recent Inquiries feed with quick actions
   - Quick Filters to narrow the feed
   - Shortcuts for CSV export, manual note, and reconciliation
3. User uses Quick Filters to focus on a subset (e.g., New Inquiries or Destinations A–Z).
4. User clicks Export CSV from dashboard to export the filtered dataset; downloads or receives a pre-signed URL.
5. User navigates to Admin Inquiry List to perform deeper filtering, search, and bulk export.
6. On Admin Inquiry List, user applies search and filters, selects multiple inquiries, and exports to CSV.
7. User opens an inquiry detail, updates status, adds internal notes, or navigates to reconciliation actions.
8. All actions reflect in real-time UI with updated counts and statuses.

---

## Technical Specifications

Data Models:
- Inquiry
  - id: string
  - guestName: string
  - destinationId: string
  - destinationName: string
  - dates: { start: string, end: string }
  - guests: number
  - status: 'New' | 'Contacted' | 'Deposit Paid' | 'Confirmed'
  - paymentStatus: 'Pending' | 'Paid' | 'Refunded'
  - amount: number
  - currency: string
  - createdAt: string
  - updatedAt: string
  - notes: string[]
- Reconciliation
  - id: string
  - inquiryId: string
  - amount: number
  - currency: string
  - status: 'Unreconciled' | 'Reconciled'
  - reconciledAt: string
  - notes: string[]
- Destination
  - id: string
  - name: string
  - slug: string
- InternalNote
  - id: string
  - inquiryId: string
  - note: string
  - authorId: string
  - createdAt: string

API Endpoints:
- GET /api/admin/inquiries
  - Query: status, destination, dateFrom, dateTo, search, page, pageSize
  - Response: { data: Inquiry[], total: number }
- GET /api/admin/reconciliations
  - Similar filters
  - Response: { data: Reconciliation[], total: number }
- POST /api/admin/export
  - Body: { type: 'inquiries' | 'reconciliations', filters?: object, format?: 'csv' }
  - Response: { url?: string, success: boolean, message?: string }
- GET /api/admin/inquiries/:id
  - Response: { data: Inquiry }
- POST /api/admin/inquiries/:id/notes
  - Body: { note: string }
  - Response: { success: boolean, note: InternalNote }
- PATCH /api/admin/inquiries/:id/status
  - Body: { status: string }
  - Response: { success: boolean, updatedInquiry: Inquiry }

Security:
- Authentication: JWT-based or session-based admin auth; require authorization header or session.
- Authorization: Only users with role 'ConciergeAdmin' can access admin endpoints.
- Validation: Validate all inputs; proper error codes for invalid parameters.

Validation Rules:
- Dates must be ISO 8601 strings; start <= end.
- Status values restricted to allowed enums.
- Amounts must be positive numbers; currency codes valid ISO 4217-like.
- Searches sanitized and do not perform raw SQL without parameterization.

---

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Admin Dashboard loads with accurate metrics and a recent inquiries feed; all data is safely rendered with null-safety guards.
- [ ] Admin Inquiry List page supports filters (status, destination, date range), search, and bulk export; data loads reliably with proper pagination.
- [ ] All array usage is guarded: (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [].
- [ ] All API responses are validated: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
- [ ] Exports generate a valid CSV file or URL, reflecting the applied filters consistently across dashboard and list pages.
- [ ] State initialization for arrays uses useState<Type[]>([]) and avoids undefined initial states.
